### Protected endpoint test — JWT bearer auth (VS Code REST Client)
#
# 1. Run the "login" request first (it captures the token via @name).
# 2. Then send the /me requests below — they reuse {{login.response.body.token}}.

@host = http://localhost:8000
@contentType = application/json


### Login to obtain a token (run this first)
# @name login
POST {{host}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret"
}


### /me WITH token (expect 200 + id/email from claims)
GET {{host}}/me
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}


### /me WITHOUT token (expect 401)
GET {{host}}/me


### /me with an invalid token (expect 401)
GET {{host}}/me
Authorization: Bearer not.a.real.token
